																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>The Smith machine is a popular workout option for fitness enthusiasts of all levels. You can perform a variety of exercises targeting multiple muscle groups for balanced development. This article describes eight Smith machine workouts offering a comprehensive approach to structuring your routine.</p>



<p>The Smith machine creates a fixed path supporting some of the loading weight. It also provides safety stops to prevent the bar from dropping below the intended range.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Some Smith machine exercises target muscles in a compound manner while others utilize an isolated approach. The Smith machine bench press activates multiple muscle groups including the chest, shoulders, and biceps.</p>



<p>Conversely, isolation exercises focus on one specific muscle group. Lifts such as the Smith machine upright row mainly target the shoulders with little support from surrounding muscles.Â Below, we discuss some valuable Smith machine workouts to increase strength and <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6950543/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">muscle hypertrophy</a>. Read on for details and guidance on performing each one.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">8 Smith Machine Exercises</p>



<p>This article provides guidance on Smith machine workouts to enhance your strength training regimen. These are eight of the best exercises to program into your split:</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Smith-Machine-Bench-Press">Smith machine bench press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Smith-Machine-Close-Grip-Press">Smith machine close-grip press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Smith-Machine-Standing-Overhead-Press">Smith machine standing overhead press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Smith-Machine-Seated-Overhead-Press">Smith machine seated overhead press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Smith-Machine-Upright-Row">Smith machine upright row.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Smith-Machine-Squat">Smith machine squat.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Smith-Calf-Raise">Smith machine calf raise.Â </a></li>



<li><a href="#Smith-Machine-Reverse-Lunge">Smith machine reverse lunge.</a></li>
</ul>



<p>They can be customized and modified to fit a variety of workout goals based on fitness level and experience.</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">8 Smith Machine Workouts</h2>



<p>The following workouts provide a comprehensive approach to target and strengthen your upper or lower body using a Smith machine. You can perform them as listed or in the order of your preference.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Smith-Machine-Bench-Press">Smith Machine Bench Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/smith-machine-bench-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Smith machine bench press</a> is an effective upper body workout targeting the arms and chest muscles. It resembles the traditional barbell bench press but the Smith machine provides additional support, reducing joint strain.</p>



<p>The Smith machine bench press is a valuable addition to your upper-body routine or <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/workouts/3-day-workout-split" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">3-day workout split</a>. It will increase chest and upper arm development.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Smith Machine Bench Press" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/977374207?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Smith Machine Bench Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start by placing a flat bench in the middle of the machine.</li>



<li>Set the bar position and safety stops. The height of the bar should be where you can comfortably reach and unhook it with straight arms.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Load the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/training/smith-machine-bar-weight" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Smith machine bar weight</a> according to your fitness goals and level, utilizing collars to secure them in place.</li>



<li>Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the floor.</li>



<li>Grip the bar slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, positioned at your mid-chest.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Slowly lower the bar towards your chest, bringing your elbows down to your sides.</li>



<li>Pause just before the bar reaches your chest to maximally activate your chest and triceps.</li>



<li>Exhale as you push back up, extending both arms to complete the rep.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Focus on maintaining control throughout the exercise. Avoid using momentum to lift and lower the bar.</li>



<li>Donâ€™t let your elbows flail outwards during the exercise to avoid pressure on your shoulder joints.</li>



<li>Concentrate on squeezing your chest and triceps at the bottom of the movement to maximize muscle activation.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">4â€“6</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8â€“12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">12+</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1â€“3 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Smith Machine Bench Press</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Smith-Machine-Close-Grip-Press">Smith Machine Close-Grip Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/smith-machine-close-grip-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Smith machine close-grip press</a> replicates the movement of the bench press but uses a narrow grip on the bar. This increases the focus on the triceps while still activating the shoulders and chest.</p>



<p>Studies show the triceps brachii can reach <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/fulltext/2017/07000/maximal_strength_performance_and_muscle_activation.15.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">40%â€“50%</a> of maximum activation during weighted tricep extension workouts. This gives us an idea of the effort the triceps exert during this exercise.Â </p>



<p>The isolated approach to the triceps facilitates upper arm sculpting and definition. The narrower grip enables increased overall training volume by using a slightly varied stimulus to the traditional press. This will support more comprehensive upper-arm development.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Smith Machine Close Grip Bench Press" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/993338323?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Smith Machine Close-Grip Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Position a flat bench in the middle of the Smith machine, with the bar at approximately chest level.</li>



<li>Adjust the bar to a height that you can comfortably unrack it to begin your set.</li>



<li>Select the weight plates that align with your fitness level and goals.</li>



<li>Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the floor.</li>



<li>Grip the bar using an overhand grip (palms facing forward and slightly upward). Your hands should be shoulder-width or slightly narrower.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>With your elbow tucked to your sides, allow them to bend, gradually lowering the bar to your chest.</li>



<li>Pause just before the bar reaches your chest and squeeze your triceps for maximum engagement.</li>



<li>Exhale as you push back up, extending both arms to complete the rep.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Donâ€™t overload the weight as this will reduce the exercise effectiveness and increase injury risk.</li>



<li>Avoid letting your elbows splay out to the sides keeping pressure off your shoulder joints.</li>



<li>Focus on inhaling and bracing your core to start and exhaling as you push up.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">4â€“6</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8â€“12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">15+</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1â€“5 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Smith Machine Close-Grip Press</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Smith-Machine-Standing-Overhead-Press">Smith Machine Standing Overhead Press</h3>



<p>The<a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/smith-machine-standing-overhead-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"> Smith machine standing overhead press</a> is a key exercise designed to build strong, defined shoulders. This movement engages the shoulder muscles and core while the Smith machine minimizes the load on the stabilizer muscles.</p>



<p>This exercise improves functional upper-body strength as the movement is used in many daily activities. Some of these involve lifting your child or carrying heavy objects. It is a great workout for both beginners and advanced lifters to achieve fitness goals.</p>



