<li>Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart. Grasp the bar with a grip slightly narrower than shoulder-width, palms facing you.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Step back slightly to clear the bar from the rack. Ensure youâ€™re close enough that the bar grazes the front of your body.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.</li>



<li>Lift the barbell straight up along your body as you take a big exhale.</li>



<li>Hold for one count when the bar reaches just below your chin with elbows fully flexed. Squeeze your shoulders to engage the muscles.</li>



<li>Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.&nbsp;</li>
